title: White
description:
Just a solid white screen, with additional colors available via the touchscreen. I use it as a flashlight.

Slide your finger around in the top third, middle third, or bottom third of the screen to change red, green and blue components of the color.

The app can be set to keep the screen on, to automatically increase the screen brightness to maxium, and to only show white (disable color changes).

comments: Literally all it does is change colors by moving or tapping your finger at certain places of the screen. I would definitely recommend this for children at the age of 3 or lower.

This app appears when searching for "white wallpaper. It should not, because it is not a wallpaper", nor will it work as wallpaper. However it does do what the longer description says. JUST DON'T Touch THE SCREEN!!!
Good handy lightbox for making paper animation.
So bright,I put some paper on my tablet's screen and it was very bright,it helps alot when you want to make a flipbook,thanks so muchüòÄüòÄüòÄ

title: White Noise Lite
description:
AS SEEN IN CONSUMER REPORTS! Find out why the world is sleeping better with White Noise Free. Features ambient sounds of the environment that will help you relax during the day and sleep great at night.

Do you have trouble going to sleep? Are you traveling on a plane and need a quick power nap? Does your newborn baby wake up in the middle of the night? There are numerous benefits to using White Noise:

‚Ä¢ Helps you sleep by blocking distractions
‚Ä¢ Relaxes and reduces stress
‚Ä¢ Pacifies fussy and crying babies
‚Ä¢ Increases focus while enhancing privacy
‚Ä¢ Soothes headaches and migraines
‚Ä¢ Masks tinnitus (ringing of the ears)

Even when you‚Äôre asleep, your brain is constantly scanning and listening for sounds. If it‚Äôs too quiet, unwanted noises such as faucet drips or police sirens can interrupt your sleep. White Noise generates sounds over a wide range of frequencies, masking those noise interruptions, so you can not only fall asleep, but stay asleep.

SOUND CATALOG

40 sounds are included as part of the application (no downloading required unless you want more) including all the color noises (brown, white, pink, etc), mechanical sounds like a bedroom fan or air conditioner, light to heavy rains, rushing water sounds, beach and ocean waves, and so much more. For the entire list of sounds please visit our website. No streaming is required for playback.

APPLICATION FEATURES
‚Ä¢ 40+ perfectly looped sounds with free downloads from the White Noise Market App and website at https://whitenoisemarket.com/
‚Ä¢ Full support for Android 7.0 (Nougat) Multi-Window
‚Ä¢ Background audio support so you can use other apps while listening
‚Ä¢ Record, loop, and share new sounds
‚Ä¢ Chromecast TV support for audio control and playback. (Note: Chromecast audio devices require using the Google Home app)
‚Ä¢ Create new soundscapes by mixing multiple noises with support for adjusting volume, balance, and pitch of each individual sound in the mix
‚Ä¢ Full screen digital clock with multiple colors and brightness controls makes it the perfect companion for any nightstand
‚Ä¢ Advanced alarm and timer system that slowly fades audio in and out so you awake naturally feeling more refreshed
‚Ä¢ On-screen media player and volume controls with swipe gesture support for navigating sound collection
‚Ä¢ Star favorite sounds and mixes in the sound catalog for quick access using the Favorite view
‚Ä¢ Designed to work on all Android-based phones and tablets
‚Ä¢ Advanced Settings let you prevent interruptions such as notifications, tweak buffer size for optimal playback, adjust sound volume, balance, pitch, custom alarm snooze times, and more. All the pro tools you need for better sleep.

MEDIA REVIEWS

CONSUMER REPORTS: Smartphone Apps Can Sound as Good as a White-Noise Machine

DR. OZ SHOW: 13 Miracles of 2013: "Revolutionary Sound App!"

WASHINGTON POST: Smartphone Puts Newborn to Sleep: "For the next four months, the infant slept with his father's phone in his crib and White Noise tuned to 'air conditioner.' The monotonous buzz kept the baby sleeping soundly and his parents happy."

CNET: Apps that can improve your life: ‚ÄúTrouble falling asleep at night? A little White Noise might do the trick.‚Äù

UPGRADE TO FULL VERSION

Download the full version of White Noise for improved audio, more alarms, and no ads. Just tap the Upgrade button in settings.

Note: "White Noise Lite" was previously known as "White Noise Free"

WHITE NOISE MARKET

Download free sleep sounds from the White Noise Market at the following URL:
https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.tmsoft.whitenoise.market

recentChanges: BACKGROUND AUDIO! Do we need to say anything more? And other minor fixes. We've updated our White Noise apps for over 10 years so that you can sleep better. Please help us continue the support by sharing White Noise Lite with friends and family on your favorite social networks. 7.6.7 Additional fixes for running when installed on SD Card. This should be fully resolved now. Thanks for supporting White Noise!
comments: My husband and I have been using this app every night for at least the passed 5 years. This app is amazing, however it has this nasty little habit every other night of randomly exiting and stopping. I'm a light sleeper so I wake up when it turns off. It will do this twice in a row, then be fine. No rhyme or reason to it.

We use this so much!! Have used this app for naps, sleeping at relatives' houses, and concentrating for work or studying. Free, non intrusive ads, and so many options. I've set all my favorites and can flip through them easily - brown noise and heavy rain are my top picks. We always sleep better when using it.

I've been using this app for years and loved it. Until recently when it started glitching all the time. I turn it on, get comfortable to sleep and then it cuts off. I turn it back on, sometimes it cuts off again minutes later. I had hoped if I put up with it for a month or so that the kinks would be fixed but nope, so here I am uninstalling.

Love this app. I've used it for about 3 or 4 years now, for sleep and studying. I would give it 5 stars except that it occassionally switches itself off during the night. That's not to big a deal for me though. I have used different sounds and sometimes switch them for a change. My current favourite is dishwasher but I've also liked shower and running water. I highly recommend the app.

I love, love, love this app. It actually calms me. I have sooo much going on with me (family matters) that I need some positive distraction. Since I've discovered this app, I can tap in anytime day or night for some "ME" time!!

title: White Screen
description: This App displays a blank white screen without requesting any permissions. Keeps your screen on unless you close it.
descriptionHTML: This App displays a blank white screen without requesting any permissions. Keeps your screen on unless you close it.
summary: White Screen  Bright Flashlight
recentChanges: Initial Release
comments: Works perfect as a lightbox to check film negatives with. Wouldn't recommend scanning with this light since you'll be able to see the pixels.

Oh my goodness I thought I was going to go INSANE trying to keep my screen lit every few seconds while taking care of my wife's low blood sugars at night. This app is perfect soft light... My phone's flashlight would be too bright for this kind of thing. It's absolutely wonderful to not have to tap the screen every 3 seconds. This is perfect. Thank you so much.
Had one single job: screen white. Tho, the virtual buttons are still visible.

Thanks a lot for introducing this app.This helps me a lot while drawing diagrams.I was looking for a white screen everytime and thought of searching it in play store actually I was not sure whether these kinds of apps exist. But I wonder when I found it. It's just not a mere thought.

Exactly what I needed: a lightbox-substitute to make it easy to transfer sewing-pattern markings to my fabric. No ads, no permissions, and nothing happens when I accidentally bump the screen. üëçüëçüëç

developerAddress: F12, No.8, Lane 28, Danba Road,Putuo District,Shanghai

comments: Great game! Not evey popular because it's an older game, but not very many ads at all because of this. Has had many updates so best version it will ever be. The only bad thing is the songs. The songs aren't the song you'll hear on the radio, but and overall great game.

This game is absolutely wonderful. Of course all free games have ads but this one doesn't constantly spam you every five seconds with an ad. Not to mention the gameplay is super fun and all the different games are very fun. I would recommend this game to everyone. It's so enjoyable and just overall an awesome game! Also it's not one of those games that you have to pay a bunch of money just to play more than two levels

Some may say that 300 modes is too much and deviated from the piano tiles mode. However, I think this is a mobile game mecca. Would love to give this five stars but the unskippable ads frustrate me. The pay option to remove ads seemingly crash the app. Given the model of my phone, this definitely seems like an app problem. Fix this and I'll rate the full five stars.

Looks awesome with a lot of features. But cant even get past 26 in arcade, which was the whole reason I downloaded it, because of a glitch.. so in all pretty disappointed. Tried contacting creators as well and nothing came up.

in my opnion this app deserves way more attention then the magic tiles that everyone loves so much. not only is there a huge lack of lagging and buffering, but with all the games and choices its so much more fun, i also love that you guys accept ideas from fans. keep up what you do :)

title: White Calling ‚Äì international calls / call abroad
description:
The White Calling app gives you low cost international calls you can rely on.

FREE credit when you install the app ‚Äì try us out!

Why the White Calling app?

The White Calling app lets you call any phone number, so reliability is great and there's no need for the other person to have the app to receive a call. In short, it‚Äôs the easiest, most reliable way to call friends and loved ones around the world.

- Lowest international call rates
- Mobile Airtime Top-up: recharge loved ones' pay-as-you-go mobiles with voice and data, all over the world
- Great call quality and reliability - calling real phone numbers, instead of app-to-app 
- Really easy to use
- More FREE credit when you invite friends to the app!


White Calling gives you three ways to call

Have monthly inclusive minutes from your mobile provider?...
Let the app call via local access number ‚Äì we route your call to your international number automatically ‚Äì giving you the best call quality and reliability
Note: local access number calling is not available in all countries
	
Call over Wi-Fi
Ideal if you are on Pay As You Go, or have poor phone reception - and perfect for when you're travelling

Call over 3G/4G
Great if you have a big monthly data allowance


Use a White Calling card?
You can add your card PIN in the app to use your card credit!

comments: Just works and is cheap to use. A couple of superficial wishes: Dark theme and integration with the Android dialer. But I'm getting crystal clear calls regardless of where I am that being Iceland, UK, Norway or Russia. There's so many apps like this that is unreliable. I do not need it often but when I do it has to work. This is.

Well, previously I gave this app 5 star and now it literally sucks. So annoying! I tried to call home (Bangladesh) at least 30/40 times and won't allow me to call! Just cut off even b4 it starts calling. If you want to get 5 star again, solve this issue with the app. Even after recent new updates, the same issues continue to disallow calls.

Tesco calling app has way cheaper rates for UK landline and mobiles, don't know why I got sucked into this app, maybe it's because the receiver don't need app to receive calls, but still rates on here to call inland is too much! Uninstalled

It works but some issues Couldn't add a calling card credit and can't seem to top up using the links on the app. Definitely works for making a call but not sure if that matters now that I'm out of credit and can't top up...

Sensational!! Very low international call rate and clear communication, no breaking voices. Top up is also very easy, with a slight touch, you top up at the comfort of you home. Overall white calling is amazing.

title: White Noise Baby
description:
Recommended by Katie Couric as an APP-solutely fabulous baby app for moms! Help your baby relax, stop crying, and sleep better.  Includes perfectly looped sounds that your baby will love such as taking a car ride, classical music, conch shell, and doppler ultrasound of the womb.

Need to quiet your baby while out in public?  Try our baby rattle that includes complex shapes and fun sounds that will be sure to entertain.  Need our sleeping sounds to activate when baby starts crying?  Our Baby Monitor will do just that. White Noise Baby has so many great features, requested from parents like you, for your baby to enjoy!

Features
- Perfectly looped ambient sounds and music to help your baby sleep
- Baby mode notification to reduce interruptions
- High Contrast Baby rattle w/ touch and shake controls to quiet a fussy baby
- Sound shutoff timer that fades volume to silence with baby monitor restart
- Baby monitor will reactivate timer and play sound if crying is detected
- Event log of noise detection helps discover your baby's sleeping cycle
- Tips to help your baby sleep great
- Safety tips from the US Consumer Product Safety Commission
- Optimized for all Android smartphones and tablets
- Battery Saver Mode for longer battery life
- Upgrade to full version to remove ads and enable background audio 

White Noise Baby helps your child sleep by blocking distractions while relaxing and reducing stress. Even when your baby is asleep, the brain is constantly scanning and listening for sounds. If it‚Äôs too quiet, unwanted noise such as a parent walking into the room or another child playing may interrupt your baby‚Äôs sleep. White Noise generates sounds over a wide range of frequencies, masking those noise interruptions, so your infant can not only fall asleep, but also stay asleep.

HD Ambient Sounds:
- Air Conditioner
- Car Ride
- Train Ride
- Truck Ride
- Conch Shell
- Doppler Ultrasound
- Hair Dryer
- Fan
- Vacuum Cleaner
- Blue Noise
- Gray Noise
- Pink Noise
- Brown Noise (aka Red Noise)
- Violet Noise
- White Noise
- Dripping Water
- Water Rumble
- Grandfather Clock
- Heartbeat
- Wind Chimes

HD Classical Music Tracks:
- Beethoven Fur Elise
- Brahms Lullaby
- Chopin Nocturne No 9
- Liszt Consolation No 6
- Tchaikovsky Sugarplum Fairy
- Chopin Impromptu
- Chopin Prelude Op 28
- Chopin Walzer
- Mozart Sonata Facile
- Mozart Sonate Op KV331

Baby Mode, if enabled, will prevent your device from being interrupted.  This helps to make sure your little one gets to sleep faster but also stays asleep.

White Noise Baby sounds are similar to gently shushing in your baby's ear.  The name is derived from white light, which is what the human eye sees when all the colors that make up the visible light spectrum are combined. Blend a red, green, and blue light together and you'll get white light. You probably have noticed if you're in a brightly lit room filled with white light, it is difficult to see colored lights. That's because those individual colors get masked by surrounding white light. In the same way, white noise has equal energy at all sound frequencies to which humans are sensitive. Other sounds will get masked by white noise so they become less detectable.

To learn more about White Noise and other White Noise sounds please visit our blog at: https://www.tmsoft.com/white-noise-player/

Safety tips provided by the US Consumer Product Safety Commission and includes important hazard information for cribs, toys, bathing aids, baby gates, high chairs, playpens, rattles, squeeze toys, teethers, toy chests, walkers, and others. 

CONTACT US

We want to hear your feedback! Please send us your suggestions and other feedback  e-mail us directly inside the app inside of settings.

Positive reviews and ratings keep the free updates coming! 

Like us on Facebook at https://www.facebook.com/whitenoiseapp

Follow us on Twitter at https://twitter.com/whitenoiseapp

Visit our Website at https://www.tmsoft.com/white-noise-baby/

comments: Paid version without ads is worth it!
Great app, saved me many a night.

Reliable and very easy to use. White noise starts straight away which is VERY useful when you need it to help calm your baby. Good variety of white noise with ability to add more. The high colour rattle is very useful when baby is fussy or has begun to get themselves worked up. Paid for the non-advert version as it's an app I use a lot of the time. Keep up the good work

Best app on the market. I've used it to sleep myself since my son slept in his own room from 12mo onwards. The past two years sleeping myself (extremely light sleeper) at night it's become a regular go to when I need comfort. I prefer oscillating fan setting on quite a low volume. Before for my son I'd always use the oscillating fan setting on a mid volume and the vacuum for instant relief calming and to clean around the house. Fantastic product. Makes my life easier.

title: White Wallpapers
description:
Keep it simple with sleek white wallpapers!


White wallpapers are the perfect way to make sure that your apps stand out! Busy colorful backgrounds take away from the truly important part of your device ‚Äì the apps you use to organize and live your life! But never fear, having a simple colorless background doesn‚Äôt have to be boring! title: Black White Interracial Dating - Interracial Match
description:
Interracial Dating: The New Enlightenment

Less than a century ago, interracial dating was something you didn‚Äôt talk about, and something to hide if you did prefer a person of a different color.  There were few places you could go to safely without causing some sort of scandal, and even fewer people who were willing to listen with understanding.  

Maybe it was the rhythm and blues saturating the basements of late night entertainment.  Maybe it was a society lifting out of the Great Depression, with more tolerance accompanying their more affluent life styles.  Maybe it was the boldness of writers, spokes people and celebrities campaigning for civil rights, but by the 1960‚Äôs, interracial dating slowly became more acceptable.  

The changing times brought its own set of problems.  Even as the work force became more integrated, with minorities and women stepping into roles once designed for white, professional males, and public places ceased separating or refusing services to minorities, interracial dating was still awkward.  It was an era of general agreement on civil rights, but there weren‚Äôt very many among the Depression Years parents who were prepared to bring racial integration into the home. 
 
The Millennial Perspective

The awkward early years of racial integration jump-started interracial dating.  Today, seven percent of the population claims a mixed race heritage.  The number is growing rapidly, with most interviewee‚Äôs stating pride in their multiracial origins and claiming their heritage has made them more open to other cultures. 
 
Seven percent is significantly higher than in the 1970‚Äôs, when only one percent declared a mixed race background, but analysts feel these number are actually only about half the actual percentage, as many who are mixed race claim only one ethnic background.  The majority of those who claim only one race are middle-aged or older.  
From Age to Regional Location

The younger you are, the easier it is to find a partner for interracial dating.  The twenty to thirty year old set are generally very casual and already have a wide mixture of multi-cultural and multi-racial friends.  Tolerance, however, especially by family and community, can vary greatly according to demographics.  In many areas, especially regions that historically disapproved of mixed race dating, there may no longer be taboos, but the cultural clash still exists.  The family, and even your date, might have stereotypical views of your personal tastes and behaviors.  

Crossing the barriers where racial misconceptions still exist takes fortitude and patience.  Interracial views are changing rapidly but not racial views.  You may experience those uncomfortable moments of somebody going out of their way not to offend you, anxieties concerning appropriate behaviors, or even suspicion and reserved behaviors.  

Unless you are dating someone with exactly the same historical background, social status and religion, you are still going to be challenged by your date‚Äôs customs.  For many races, the customs are more engrained than color, status or ancestral origins.  Religion may be an important influence on their lives, even if they no longer declare a religious preference, as they will make time for the traditional values of their family. 
 
But that‚Äôs part of what interracial dating is all about.  It‚Äôs an opportunity to take a broader look at the world around us, to improve our communications with others, and learn about differing cultures and customs that can enrich our everyday lives.

description:

Thanks so much for the reviews. We add and remove features based on what you guys say. We read and appreciate every one of them. 

Interested in helping us translate White Light into your language? head to https://hexinnovation.com/WhiteLight/Translate

Are you an Android developer? Do you want to download the source? Check out our repository at https://github.com/hexinnovation/WhiteLight

Features:
‚Ä¢ White Light doesn't need any permissions except access to the camera (so it can use the phone's flash) and permission to start when you restart or power on your phone (so it can display a persistent notification without you having to open the app first).
‚Ä¢ Turn on the flashlight from the lock screen with a widget or notification
‚Ä¢ Activate phone's flashlight with a swipe
‚Ä¢ A configurable notification can be used to turn the flashlight off or on
‚Ä¢ Light stays on even when the screen is off
‚Ä¢ Resizable home screen widget
‚Ä¢ Light or dark theme
‚Ä¢ Adjust screen brightness (for times when the flash is too bright).

recentChanges:
Version 2.0.1 - 2.0.3:
‚Ä¢ Increased compatibility
‚Ä¢ Bug fixes

2.0:
‚Ä¢ A notification is shown that allows you to turn on the light. This can be set to always visible, never visible, or only visible at the lock screen. This requires a new permission (start when Android starts) to show the notification as soon as your phone turns on, before you open the app.
‚Ä¢ Setting to disable shutting off the light when the screen turns off

comments: i like that its accessible to turn on or off without needing to unlock the phone. BUT. 1) several times the light was on when i pulled it out from a pocket. 2) it randomly flocks on and off! very frustrating. no apparent pattern sometimes it flicks back kn immediately, sometimes it waits for deep and imaginative cursing to ensue from me kicking something i suddenly cant see. its a brand new phone (S9+), it does it fully charged or almost used or anywhere between. i tried, but it had to go.

The app is perfect as it gives full power of the torch light and also works from the notification panel on lock screen. The issue with the notification panel is if the app closes for a certain amount of time. The notification of the torch light disappears and requires user to open the app again. This issue can be fixed via an update, however this is the perfect app I have seen without ads.

the screen will for some reason always brighten up ridiculously high when you turn on the light and you'll have to manually turn it down (still brighter than the lowest setting on my phone, which is my preference) the fact that you have to also manually turn off the light even if you put the phone in sleep mode or close out the app is also a nuisance. My preferred flash light app before this one decided to forcefully play ads so at least this one has that going for it.

It does work as a flashlight, but i really wanted the lockscreen widget and was disappointed that it doesn't work/appear on the lockscreen. My phone is old though (note2), so that might be the prob. Hope us old phone users get the same feature if it works for newer phones.

No ads, weighs less than 1 MB, no weird permissions (just camera, as it should be), free... just a terrific app. UI is nice too, and while I do not use the widget, it's still a nice option to have. Well done!

comments: Only been using it a couple hours but I'm quite impressed and cant say as I find any issues at all. I suggest trying it out!

Great app for post processing colour to b&w with lots of preset effects. No problems saving. Clean UI. Like it a lot.
Great app, easy to use and the results are dynamic.

title: White Noise Baby Sleep Sounds
description:
White Noise Baby Sleep Sounds free app helps your baby (and you!) to fall asleep using classic monotonous sounds ("white noise") proven to be effective by generations of parents.

Simply select the desired sound or create your own mix using these HD sounds:

‚úî Pure white noise 
‚úî Pure pink noise 
‚úî Waterfall (natural brown noise) 
‚úî Fan 
‚úî Air conditioner
‚úî Vacuum cleaner 
‚úî Hair dryer 
‚úî Washing machine 
‚úî Boiling kettle
‚úî Shower 
‚úî Bath filling
‚úî Sea 
‚úî Rain 
‚úî Thunderstorm
‚úî Wind
‚úî Creek 
‚úî Mountain river 
‚úî Fireplace 
‚úî Airplane
‚úî Train 
‚úî Car 
‚úî Cat purring
‚úî In the womb 
‚úî Mother 
‚úî Heartbeat 

From practical experience, we have learned that such white noise sounds are more effective as a lullaby for baby sleep than music, tones or sing.
Babies love white noise. Background white noise is calming for baby and resembles the kind of sounds that he would hear in the womb. 

This app can also be used as a sound machine (white noise machine) by adults suffering with insomnia or sleep disorders.
The masking effect of white noise is also great for relaxation, concentration and study.

App features:
‚úî 28 white noise sounds
‚úî 4 baby lullabies
‚úî Infinite playback
‚úî Timer with soft fade out
‚úî Mixer with support for adjusting the volume of each sound in the mix
‚úî Background audio support
‚úî No full-screen ads
‚úî Offline working
‚úî Lightweight and easy to use

We do highly recommend not putting the phone closer to the baby than necessary.

comments: Love this app, and I've been using it to calm down my son when he's fussy or needing to sleep. I would ask for two improvements. 1. Please add a function to turn off the sound from the notification shade (and lock screen) 2. Please add an option to fade the sounds in and out when pressing the play or stop buttons (it's a bit sudden as it is) Thank you for a wonderful app

This has saved my sanity!! Great app!! You can costumize the sounds and its volume and also combine sounds. I found a combination that makes my son close his eyes automatically!! And I have other white sound gadgets at home, but nothing like this!! Thanks for creating it!! NOTE: Timer is in minutes not in seconds.

I use the rain sound and have been sleeping very hard. We live in the country so we don't have a lot of car noise but our walls and windows are paper thin so we still hear everything that goes on at the neighbor's house right next door. Since I started using this app last week, my husband and I have both been sleeping better since it drowns out all that random noise. We don't even hear the roosters when they start crowing.

Been using it a LONG time, loved it and the sound mixing is great, but it randomly shuts off and wakes me up - more and more lately. Turning off all phone data and wifi connections is not an acceptable solution for me. Would've been 5 stars but now it's time to move on.

Great, when it works This app just r!randomly shuts off for no reason. Sometimes it works for hours, other times it shuts off after 5 minutes. I have tried the infinite setting and 8 hours but it seems like just as I'm about to fall asleep, it shuts off, waking me up again. Getting pretty frustrated with it.

title: White Spots
description:
White Spots, A journey to the end of the Internet

Do you ever feel the desire to step out of the information flows that surround us? The White Spots App visualizes the invisible electromagnetic cloud that we live in and offers a way out. It let's you experience offline life in both Virtual and Physical Reality.

Use the app with Google cardboard to travel from the connected to the unconnected world in Virtual Reality, or use the White Spots map to explore the unconnected world yourself.

The VR mode shows the invisible world of digital signals around you and takes you on a journey to the unconnected world though a series of immersive 360¬∫ stories.

In Map mode, the high res White Spots map shows the global divide between the connected and the unconnected word. Browse the map to explore stories about offline life from people around the world or venture into uncharted territory yourself using the White Spots Route Planner.

The Route Planner finds a route to a White Spot near you and invites you to add new stories to the map.

Download the app and join the global expedition to the end of the Internet.

Book a taxi in under 10 seconds and experience exclusive priority service from Black & White Cabs

You can place the booking directly on our map, and see how many available cars there are.

No standing in the rain. Track your car as it arrives on a map, or call the driver when they are nearby. No more guessing where your cab might be.

Place bookings hours, days or weeks in advance. Whenever it's convenient for you.

If necessary, cancel your booking at any time. It takes seconds to place a new booking directly from the handy favourites list.

Having integrated SMS booking, we've now launched this intelligent Android App so you can book a taxi within 3 screen taps.

Black & White cabs is FREE to download and it costs you nothing to register.

----------------------------------------

It's so easy and quick to use. Download the App and register just once. Our intelligent software will suggest your favourite Pick Up locations, and you're ready to book your a car.

When you make a bookings, we'll notify you by Push Notification as your car is dispatched. We'll also inform you when your car is 2 minutes away, giving you additional details such as registration number, make, model and vehicle colour.

----------------------------------------

You can place the booking directly on our map, and see how many available cars there are.

No standing in the rain. Track your car as it arrives on a map, or call the driver when they are nearby. No more guessing where your cab might be.

Place bookings hours, days or weeks in advance. Whenever it's convenient for you.

Having integrated SMS booking, we've now launched this intelligent Android App so you can book a taxi within 3 screen taps.

----------------------------------------

----------------------------------------

We value feedback and take all reviews very seriously. So please leave us feedback about your journey using the App. This helps us continually improve our service.

comments: Looks like great app! However I can not find a way to set the focal length (crop factor), which is crucial for me. Downloaded this app today. Took like three pictures with it and immediately purchased the filter sets and texture sets. This is my camera now! This is amazing! Lifelong photographer and used 35 millimeter my whole life and always preferred black and white, but I've struggled to find my place in digital photography until now. Highly recommend this app to anyone serious about black and white photography, especially with a smartphone! THIS IS YOUR APP! Thank you so much for this gamechanger!!

Nice b&w photography. But it's buggy (android 9, LG) Too often a previously taken photo somehow gets randomly overlaid on the shooting preview window obscuring what you're trying to photograph...what is that all about?!

title: CRADLE White Eye Detector
description: The White Eye Detector app helps parents detect the appearance of white eye in pictures of their children. A white pupil can be a normal photographic effect in pictures (like red eye, but white). White eye can also be a symptom of multiple serious eye diseases such as retinoblastoma, pediatric cataract, and Coats' disease. These diseases are often first detected by parents because the parent notices white eye in pictures of their children. This app will find pictures on your phone or tablet that have white eye, and will show you these pictures so that you can inspect them for yourself.

Also in order to get complete scan you have to keep your App open and soon you switch or open any other app it stopped working. Just downloaded the app., haven't tested it yet. But in the introduction part at the start of App, Amblyopia, Strabismus and Refractive error are mentioned as common causes of Leukocoria. These aren't common causes but are consequences of Leukocoria. Common causes are cataract, retinoblastoma, Coats disease, persistent hyperplastic primary vitreous to name a few.

Thank you for playing The White Door! We fixed a few bugs in this new version.
comments: As a newcomer to the series I must admit I really enjoyed this game. Even though I'm sure I missed some references, the story is quite self explanatory (although tending to surrealism occasionally). Unfolded in several days, the first ones work as an introduction to the mechanics and characters, while the rest shed more and more light on what has happened to our main character. The difficulty of the puzzles progressively increases but it never feels too hard, making overall a great experience.

I'm a big fan of these weird little games. Personally, I found this one slightly easier to follow than some of the past ones. I didn't have to resort to any hints. Not one! Although I'm not 100% sure if that's a comment on my ability or the structure of the game, I definitely found this one easier to follow, whilst still being a nice little challenge. Well done, devs - keep 'em coming!

Okish. Well done for trying something different. I imagine it's hard changing from a tried and trusted pattern. Rusty Lake are by far my favourite games but I didn't enjoy this one for the reasons mentioned in other reviews. You had set a very high benchmark. Keep up the good work!

I am consistently surprised, delighted, (and frustrated in a good way), by rusty lake-the artistry, storytelling that loops back on itself, sheer creativity and ingenuity of the games. I cant play other games. I dont mind that its shorter, love new format. And dude complaining about cost, really? Less than a movie or coffee and 3x more interesting. These artists/programmers should be paid well for consistent high quality and all that goes into conceptualizing and building them. Well done.

Having played all the other Rusty Lake games I found this one a bit underwhelming. The others were fantastic. This is the first one of theirs I've paid for so was expecting much better. The minimalistic line drawings used for the majority of the game felt like lazyness throughout, and most of the puzzles were super easy. There's large parts that don't feel like a game at all but an animated story you have to prod to proceed.

PPT RESOURCES
Four different Adventist PowerPoint Resources have been made available to help pastors, evangelists and teachers to easily share various Bible topics with diverse groups of people. 

IN-BUILT BIBLE
The WTM App comes with inbuilt open software KJV Bible that will enable you to easily verify a Bible quotation without having to go online. 

SEARCH BUTTON
When you open the Bible Study or Blog section of the App, you will find a white search button fixed in a black round background on the down right corner of the App. You can use this button to easily find various Bible topics of interest.

SHARE BUTTON 
When you open a particular write-up in the Bible Study or Blog section of the App, you will find a share button on the top right corner. Press on the button to share the write-up through various accessible social media networks. You can also long press in the write-up, select all, copy and then paste to share.

SIDE NAVIGATOR
The Mobile App has one major navigator that can be activated by pressing the menu button or swiping from the left edge of your screen.

MANAGING FILES
Every study item arranged as a list (except SOP Documents) has gotten an options icon (a three-dot vertical icon) to the far right.
Pressing this icon will show several options to manage the attached files.

For SOP Documents, just press on the item to reveal the options.

SLIDE PICTURES
Several slide pictures with inspirational Bible quotes have been positioned on the main interface of the App. You may scroll through the slide pictures to read and ponder over the Bible texts. It is our prayer that the Lord will use these inspirational Bible quotes to encourage you, and also deepen your faith in Him. 

NOTIFICATIONS
This App comes with three alerts: 
‚Ä¢	777 Prayer Alerts. This alert shows up at 7:00 am and 7:00 pm. The alert serves as a reminder for us to join the prayer chain of God's people around the globe.

title: EGW Writings
description:
Ellen G. White is the most widely published Seventh-day Adventist author. Her ministry spanned 70 years, from 1844 until 1915. Guided by the Holy Spirit, she exalted Jesus and pointed to Scripture as the basis of one's faith. Ellen White wrote on a wide variety of spiritual and practical topics, from spiritual, to health, education, ministry, financial and marital advice. Her best known most translated work is Steps to Christ, followed by the 5 conflict of the ages series: Patriarchs and Prophets, Prophets and Kings, Desire of Ages, Acts of the Apostles, and The Great Controversy. Ellen G. White is also credited as the co-founder of the Seventh-day Adventist Church
EGW Writings for Android enables you to download The Complete Published Writings of Ellen G. White. This free app is available for Android v.2.2 through v.4.4. The EGW Writings app allows users to download the books individually or as a collection. It is available in 9 languages: Chinese, English, French, German, Italian, Portuguese, Romanian, Russian, and Spanish. The App is great for reading EGW Writings or for word and phrase searches within an individual book or your entire library. The Study Center allows you to create topical folders for bookmarks, highlights, and for creating your own notes. The app also includes 7 Bible versions in English for direct linking to Bible references within Ellen White's writings. The app includes a contemporary dictionary of Ellen White: Noah Webster‚Äôs 1828 American Dictionary. A special feature of this app is live streaming of available MP3 audio books in all languages via www.egwwritings.org website. It also has Text-To-Speech (TTS) audio player for listening to audiobooks of any content in the EGW Writings app.

comments: Gives the minimalist look that you need. Pretty good library of icons. A lot are missing but I often find a good replacement. I use it with Microsoft launcher and it works perfectly.

I love the icons. Just the look I wanted. Plain white icons like the default Android notification icons however unlike other icon sets this one has some personality. The icons look a bit more energetic and edgy rather than plain and boring. There's a lot of apos that weren't covered, but there's tons of icons to choose from so that doesn't matter much. Thank you for making my phone look amazing!

I love the icon look but half of them aren't themed. I wanted a full monochromatic look and even basic built in apps like the gallery don't have the theme applied. Nice icons for the ones that are themed, but overall I'd say this was really half-assed.

Thank you for create thiis. I love this app. i like flat design on it. it's nice guys, simply icon. looks more elegance for my phone. please, add more office stuff icon like a computer, book/document, design materials, or more and i hope this version still free :D
I personally use this side-by-side with Whicons cuz this icon pack simply isn't enough as there is a limited number of icons. It's good when used with Whicons to replace any ugly icons.

Upload your existing White Noise recordings and mixes to share your audio experiences with the entire White Noise community. Popular sounds available from the market include:

Login with your favorite social network to download unlimited sounds, upload your recordings, send hearts, and post comments. Guest login is also supported but limited to only a few downloads per day.

comments: I've been using this for quite some time. I have enjoyed it when I have used it. BUT, my chief complaint is that it does not allow the user to delete sound files. The "ACTIONS" section under the menu should include a DELETE function. There are a few dozen files I would delete because I'll never use them. Including these makes the list far too long. Being able to delete those I don't like would result in a 5-star rating.
It will be better if the app has the search button. I can't able to find my favourite sounds.

White Noise Lite is fantastic app that functions beautifully, allows you to create your own mix, and upload your own sounds to the ever expanding WNL community. Become a part of #WhiteNoiseLite and start creating! -Patrick ‚ù§

It does what it says and I was a fan of it for six months. A word of warning though. My use was a sleep aid for external disturbing noises. I found some soft on-ear sleep headphones and the "babbling brook" etc was just wonderful. The audio level I used was low, I could easily for example have a conversation whilst listening. - Despite this, some months in I started to wake up with tinnitus. Sometimes it would last all day ir longer and was very worrying. I had to ditch the app I really liked, and fortunately the problem went away within a few weeks. Morale? - take a lot of care, Noise levels while awake are handled by the ears and brain (IMO) quite differently to when asleep.

I bought the premium version of this app when I was in college - I have disabilities that made studying very difficult and focusing nearly impossible. This app saved my life - it really allows you the distraction of the white noise to focus on your actual work. Very soothing, now using for my LSAT prep! 10/10 recommend!

title: EGW Writings 2
description:
Ellen G. White is the most widely published Seventh-day Adventist author. Her ministry spanned 70 years, from 1844 until 1915. Guided by the Holy Spirit, she exalted Jesus and pointed to Scripture as the basis of one's faith. Ellen White wrote on a wide variety of spiritual and practical topics, from spiritual, to health, education, ministry, financial and marital advice. Her best known most translated work is Steps to Christ, followed by the 5 conflict of the ages series: Patriarchs and Prophets, Prophets and Kings, Desire of Ages, Acts of the Apostles, and The Great Controversy. Ellen G. White is also credited as the co-founder of the Seventh-day Adventist Church.
EGW Writings 2, v.5.0.0 for Android, enables you to download The Complete Published Writings of Ellen G. White. This free app is available from Android OS v.4.2.0 and up. The EGW Writings 2 app allows users to download books individually or as a complete collection. The user interface (UI) menus now support 16 languages: Arabic, Chinese, English, French, German, Indonesian, Italian, Korean, Polish, Portuguese, Romanian, Russian, Spanish, Swahili, Tagalog, and Ukrainian. In addition, the app has EGW books in 98 languages that you can download or read online.

App Features:
- Syncing of Study Center data and user history through EGW Cloud
- My Library
- Updated bookshelf layout
- Updated reader layout
- Additional color themes
- Easy install wizard
- Vertical scrolling option or horizontal page scrolling
- Swipe right/left to move to next/previous chapter for vertical/horizontal mode
- Database storage location can be moved from internal device memory to an External SD Card
- Quick access to All Collections via side menu
- Bookshelf menu has 6 layout options in settings and a default.
- Bookshelf quick access scrollbar with A-Z or 1-9 slide info to all book lists
- User interface (UI) navigation and app speed optimization
- Offline search mode (globe)
- Optional Wifi only mode and airplane mode to save user data
- Auto update of search results when switching from online to offline
- Auto update of bookshelf to display only downloaded books when offline
- Improved search ability to go directly to a book/page/paragraph, i.e. sc 44.2
- Help icon added to search box with search syntax examples
- Improved text selection UI. Double tap for sliders and long tap for single or multi-word selection across pages. Tap and slide finger across text for multiple word selection.
- Split screen view can now maximize to full screen view and back again
- Book reader chapter progress indicator scrollbar added 
- Pre-recorded audiobooks collection added to main bookshelf
- Listening History added to bookshelf menu to keep track of your audiobooks
- Maximum font size increased to 72 points
- Downloading books to Internal Memory has been optimized for multi-threaded quick downloads of all collections. Please note that Google Android OS limits downloads to one book at a time for External SD storage cards. So it could take days to download all the books to your Ext. SD Card. We suggest downloading all the books to your internal memory first (if you have the space) and then transferring the books to your SD Card by going to the side menu>Settings>Database location>tap switch> then choose Ext. SD Card>OK.

comments: The app is so good, but have some software flaws, like you can't clear search history... And also I like the young man voice in the audio version of "Christ object lesson," it is clear and decent. The old man's bass voice in some of the audio version aren't that good, and some of it has background noises. If possible let all voice reading be done by the young man voice, or and option for someone to download from that voice which him/her prefers.

This app has many good qualities. However, it also has some technical flaws, which is why it's not worth 5 stars imo. 1. Search engine problems. It fails to search words when the EGW periodical reference is specified. Ditto for Letters/Manuscripts 2. The search engine function does not work at all for any of the pioneer writings. You cannot type in a code and page number to jump to a specific paragraph, or search key words. 3. Upon exiting the app, it forgets your place and I must renavigate.

I truly cherish this app. Having all of the spirit of prophecy books at my fingertips is priceless. I love that I can highlight and save special passages in the study center. The search feature allows me to look up hard to find passages for which I can only recall a word or phrase & this is one of the things I truly appreciate about this app. Once in a while, it may freeze but it's never a huge issue and doesn't last for long. The daily subscriptions are a plus. Very easy to use & nicely done.

This app meets most of my expectations. It is certainly better than the previous one and its search function works much better. The ability to bookmark and also save highlighted references so I can easily find them and return to them later is very good. The only drawback I have discovered is there is no way that I found so far to bookmark the audio books to go back later and continue listening where I left off. When I reopen the app it wants to start at the beginning of the chapter

I wish it saved where I've left off listening. I enjoy listening to the books but it won't pick up where I stopped listening. One time I was listening in the car and switched to my bluetooth because I was getting out and as soon as I cut the car off the app stopped playing in my ear, jumped to the beginning of the book on my phone and did nothing. I had to manually go to the chapter and try to remember the time stamp. Is there anyway to fix this? I use the galaxy Note 8.

title: Baby Sleep - White Noise
description:
Babies love white noise. They have spent 9 months in the quite loud womb so they are used to "noise". Background white noise is actually calming for your baby and resembles the kind of sounds that he would hear in the womb.

The app contains great selection of soothing white noise and lullabies. It has a simple timer that saves your battery. In addition to that it contains calming "shh-shhhh" sounds recorded by parents. The app does not require internet connection so you can use wherever you are.

‚òÖ White noise reduces stress in babies
‚òÖ White noise helps babies to sleep

comments: When it works it's great. But it constantly STOPS WORKING AND WON'T START AGAIN.... baby awake! In response to your comment, in can have been on only a matter of minutes before it stops. And with no other apps running.

I used to like this app, but now I have ads popping up when I'm clicking from one noise to another. You have to try and exit out of it or wait for it to finish. My screaming baby doesn't want to wait for the ad to finish. Will be uninstalling

I don't know if it was a coincidence but I downloaded this at 5am as a desperate attempt and put the heartbeat sound on for my twins and we all slept for a solid three hours. I love that you can keep it on continuously or set a timer. And that you can lock your phone or go to different apps it keeps going.

$39 CAD for an ad-free version? Insanity. Also, I have the suspicion that the developer copies designs from other white noise apps and has submitted dozens of clones to Google Play, all of which charge $39. :(
I like the nature sounds on here as well as the other white noise sounds. The lullabies need a bit more diversity. I use this all the time for bub.

title: White Noise: Sleep Sounds
description:
White noise, sleep sounds and meditation music are best for relaxing, sleeping, meditation and concentration or if you have problems with tinnitus or insomnia.

You can now forget about insomnia and start sleeping better. White noise or brown noise sounds are specifically designed to overcome insomnia by taking your mind into a deep state of relaxation.

You can set the timer and put your app in background or turn off the screen. At the end of the time, the sound fades gently and the application closes by itself. So you do not have to worry about closing the white noise app if you fall asleep. White noise is an ideal application for learning, reading, concentration, meditation and rest.

For a better experience, we recommend you the use of headphones or earphones to listen the relaxing sounds.

Application features:
- 30 relaxing sounds with white noise,
- helps you sleep by blocking distracting sounds,
- timer system that slowly fades audio out,
- auto-pause sounds on incoming call,
- usage in the background and with other apps,
- no streaming is required for playback (no data connection required),
- you can make list of favorite sounds.

Natural white noise relaxing sounds:
- Cicadas sounds,
- Fireplace,
- Heavy rain,
- Sound of the night,
- Ocean waves,
- Thunderstorm,
- Snowstorm,

- Wind noise,

title: Screen Light Red White
description:
For phones, tablets and devices without a camera LED.

Use your screen as a torch.
White color for normal use. Red color for non-blinding.
Switch colors by tapping on the rectangle.
Automatically brightens the screen and returns to your setting.
Does not use the camera LED.
Suitable for tablets and phones, all screen sizes.
Supports android 2.2 up

Free. No Ads. No Permissions.
Suitable for all screen sizes.

Useful for night navigation, map reading, orienteering, rogaining, and just playing around in the dark.

Warning: not suitable for use as a photographic safelight.
 - LCD screens have a white backlight and you can expect leakage at all wavelengths. 
 - OLED red LEDs emit some light below 600nm

Problems, suggestions, requests: send by email to developer
Source code: github.com/kodintent/RedWhiteScreenBright

comments: I like this app, but can you update the bug that makes it switch from red to white when the screen rotates please!
Did not work. Kept turning off red light and going to white. uninstalled.
Simple no adds. Exactly what I was looking for. THANK YOU.

It's a simple enough app. A bright red or white screen with the ability to switch between the two. Unfortunately when you tilt the phone, which you do quite often when you hold it like a light, it switches from red back to bright white. Really annoying. If it were not for this it would be great.

I never would have thought that such a simple app would be one of the most useful tools I could ask for when looking after a 4 week old baby! The red light is ideal for sleeping, we have it on all night (sometimes on 2 phones). Its enough light to allow us to keep an eye on the little one but still get to sleep ourselves. With a simple touch of the screen we can pop on the white light for feeding, winding, changing, etc. A big thank you to the developer for making a very tough job just a tiny bit easier.

title: Ellen G. White Devotionals/ Audio Books
description:
Ellen Gould White was an author and an American Christian pioneer. Along with other Sabbatarian Adventist leaders such as Joseph Bates and her husband James White, she formed what became known as the Seventh-day Adventist Church. Wikipedia
Born: 26 November 1827, Gorham, Maine, United States
Died: 16 July 1915, Elmshaven, Deer Park, California, United States
Buried: 26 August 1915, Oak Hill Cemetery
Children: William C. White, Edson White, Henry Nichols White, John Herbert White
Quotes
The words of the Bible, and the Bible alone, should be heard from the pulpit.
Talk unbelief, and you will have unbelief; but talk faith, and you will have faith. According to the seed sown will be the harvest.
The Bible is our rule of faith and doctrine.

Devotionals

Steps to Christ By Ellen G. White
The Acts Of The Apostles By  Ellen G. White

comments: After using for two years, the latest version stopped working for me. Now it stops playing randomly during the night, both temporarily for a few seconds, and worse, finally stopping completely after 30 to 40 minutes. I don't have the timer on, do not have any other apps running, and the behavior is the same on multiple devices running different OS versions (8 and 9), so it is clearly a bug recently introduced to the code.

I have used this app for at least a year, and until recently it was great. It seems with the change to making this a paid app the free version has gained some issues. Specifically the issue I am having is the app will suddenly stop all sound about 15 minutes after you start it, just in time for you to be almost asleep, then jolted awake by sudden silence. I'll be looking for another app today.

I would give it a 5 star a year ago. But now its full of ads. Plus to that i cant use it anymore. It gives an error after 10-15 seconds every time i open it says it stopped working. If i press "ok" the program shuts down. But if i press "report" it keeps working. A weird way to force your users to purchase stuff. Would gave it a 0 if i could right now. Edit: To make it even worse, the app starts playing random music now. It doesnt go away until you shut the app. Which makes the app useless.

This app is perfect. I use it every night. Being able to customize which sounds you like together and the individual volume of each is so wonderful. I tend to use brown noise, at a low volume, with the rain at a medium. There is a sleep timer function as well! I never review apps really, but I had to recommend this app. 10/10

This is the best app that I ever use it when I want to study. I've tried listening to music, other similar apps but this is the app that I highly recommended. I voted 4 stars because I like to have pink noise but this app doesn't have it. If you added pink noise inside I'll be giving 5 stars.
